<HEADLINE>
UPDATE: Chinese Catholics sends condolence letter mourning death of
pontiff
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Catholic Patriotic Association
of China and the Chinese Catholic Bishops College sent a telegram 
Sunday morning to Vatican to express "deep condolence" over the 
demise of Pope John Paul II.
</P>
<P>
"It is very sorrowful to know that Pope John Paul II has passed
away at the call of God, to rest in Lord for good," the telegraph 
reads. "It would be a great loss for the pastoral and evangelical 
works of the Universal Church."
</P>
<P>
"We sincerely express our deep condolence, on behalf of more 
than 5 million clergies and faithfuls of the Catholic Church in 
China, and pray God grant him an eternal reward," it reads.
</P>
</TEXT>
